fields.description:
The information on the Sprint field when using the *Get issue* endpoint (/rest/api/3/issue/<issue-key>) is not so easily parsable. Example:
{code}"customfield_<id>": [
  "com.atlassian.greenhopper.service.sprint.Sprint@<id-number>[id=<sprint-id>,rapidViewId=<board-id>,state=ACTIVE,name=<sprint-name>,goal=<sprint-goal>,startDate=<start-date>,endDate=<end-date>,completeDate=<complete-date>,sequence=<sequence-id>]"
    ],{code}

It would be helpful if the information on this field could be expressed in a more user-friendly manner, similar to the *Get sprint* endpoint (/rest/agile/1.0/sprint/<sprint-id>).

The workaround we suggest is to try to parse the sprint id from the current value for the custom field sprint and use the endpoint from the agile REST API.

{panel:title=Motivation}
I'm reopening a previous feature request JSWCLOUD-9928 that was closed a few years ago. Maybe now, we can revisit this.
{panel}

Need functionality to move tickets automatically to board if we make the status change.

For example:

If the ticket is in backlog which is in Todo state, if we make to In-Progress, it should move to the board as well.;
